The paper proposes a novel architecture for deep reinforcement learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of neural eligibility traces and modulated Hebbian networks is inspired by neuroscience, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of neural engineering (cs.NE). The focus on decision making and control suggests that the paper may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural engineering (cs.NE).
